text: she was thought so beautiful many
couldn't believe her looks weren't
natural but six x-rays and a medical
file to be sold at auction appear to

the items to the unnamed seller the
doctor started the file in the late
1950s when the actress complained about
a chin deformity the notes say a
cartilage implant in her chin had begun
to dissolve they also document a
rhinoplasty procedure on the tip of her
nose nobody ever really thought about
Marla monroe having plastic surgery it
was all the speculation did she or
didn't she they thought she was such a
natural beauty they didn't want to
believe and it was also at that time
going back to the 1950s people didn't go
for plastic surgery procedures this is
very very new but again marna when role
was always cutting-edge the x-rays are
from June 1962 just two months before
the actress died from an overdose her
details were recorded under the name
Joan Newman the items are expected to
fetch between twenty and thirty thousand
dollars when they go under the hammer in
Beverly Hills next month three years ago
a set of x-rays of Monroe's chest sold
